<TITLE> 25 injured in BCL factional clashes in DU </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 2 (bdnews24.com)  Two factions of Bangladesh Chhatra League at Dhaka University clashed over establishing supremacy in Sir AF Rahman Residential Hall in the early hours of Tuesday, leaving 25 students injured. Police arrested BCL president of the hall unit Sayeduzzaman Faruk in this connection. According to witnesses, the clash erupted at around 1am while Faruk's supporters were trying to board a student in the room of BCL hall unit general secretary Mehdi Hasan. The two groups of BCLthe students front of ruling Awami Leagueattacked and chased each other with machetes, clubs and hockey sticks. They also lobbed flaming bottles at each other filling them with petrol and vandalised at least 20 rooms in the hall, campus sources said. Several rounds of firearm shots were also heard, they said, adding that the rampage caused tension among BCL activists in other halls. Armed police entered the hall at around 2am and forcibly dispersed the battling factions of the students. They used 20 rounds of teargas shells to disperse them, police said. Among the injured were the hall unit general secretary Mehdi Hasan and BCL cadres Omar Faruk, Aminul Islam and Saju. They were admitted to university medical centre and Dhaka Medical College Hospital. DU proctor Saiful Islam Khan told bdnews24.com that he visited the hall on hearing the news. "We are trying to control the situation," he said. bdnews
